And give your daughter explicit permission to say something like: &quot;I
really don't want you to quiz me.&quot; And to change the subject.

Adults, and even other kids, seem to feel free to quiz all sorts of kids
and intrude into their lives in all sorts of rude ways.

Imagine how this conversation would go if it were your husband being
quizzed by some stranger instead of your child.

Nance

